AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this "Agreement"), is entered into as of July 27, 2022 (the "Effective Date"), by and among Black Mesa Energy, LLC, an Idaho limited liability company (together with its successors and permitted assigns, "Black Mesa"), Black Mesa Interconnection, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and permitted assigns, "Black Mesa Interconnection") and Idaho Power Company, an Idaho corporation (together with its successors and permitted assigns, "Idaho Power", and together with Black Mesa and Black Mesa Interconnection, the "Parties" and each a "Party") and amends and restates in its entirety that certain Shared Facilities Agreement by and between Black Mesa and Idaho Power entered into as of February 16, 2022, as amended by that certain First Amendment thereto dated as of June 16, 2022. RECITALS WHEREAS, Black Mesa is developing and will own and operate a 40 MWac ground-mounted photovoltaic solar power generation facility and collector substation located in Elmore County, Idaho (the "Black Mesa Project"); WHEREAS, Idaho Power will own and operate a 40 MWac / 160 MWh battery energy storage facility co-located with the Black Mesa Project (the "Idaho Power Energy Storage Project"), integrated into the Black Mesa Project and utilizing the Shared Facilities (as defined below) to interconnect under the Black Mesa GIA (together with the Black Mesa Project, the "Projects" and each a "Project"); WHEREAS Black Mesa and Idaho Power are parties to that certain Power Purchase Agreement, dated as of February 16, 2022, (as amended, supplemented or otherwise modified from time to time, and together with any other subsequent offtake arrangement for the Black Mesa Project, the "PPA"); WHEREAS, Black Mesa entered into that certain Standard Large Generator Interconnection Agreement, by and between itself and Idaho Power, dated as of August 26, 2021, as amended by that certain First Amendment thereto, dated February 23, 2022 (the "Black Mesa GIA") which provides for interconnection to the Transmission System (as defined in the Black Mesa GIA) for the Projects; WHEREAS, interconnection rights under the Black Mesa GIA are necessary both for Black Mesa to satisfy its obligations under the PPA and for Idaho Power to operate the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project; WHEREAS, Black Mesa owns certain personal property, fixtures, equipment, facilities (including the Interconnection Customer's Interconnection Facilities, as identified in the Black Mesa GIA, Appendix A,), and other rights described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the "Shared Facilities") that are necessary to interconnect the Projects to the electric transmission system of Idaho Power; WHEREAS, pursuant to that certain Assignment and Assumption Agreement, entered into prior to the execution hereof, by and between Black Mesa and Black Mesa Interconnection, Black Mesa assigned all of its right, title and interest in and to the Black Mesa GIA and the Shared Facilities, and Black Mesa Interconnection accepted such assignment and assumed all of the liabilities and obligations of Black Mesa under the Black Mesa GIA and with respect to the Shared Facilities, subject to the terms and conditions set forth therein. WHEREAS, Black Mesa Interconnection, Black Mesa and Idaho Power are entering into this Shared Facilities Agreement as contemplated under the PPA and Black Mesa GIA to use Shared Facilities and Transmission Provider's Interconnection Facilities ("TPIF"), as described in the Black Mesa GIA, to allow (i) both the Black Mesa Project and the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project to interconnect to the electric Transmission System (as defined in the Black Mesa GIA) under the terms and conditions of the Black Mesa GIA; (ii) the delivery of energy from the Black Mesa Project to either the Idaho Power Energy Storge Project or to the Idaho Power transmission system, and (iii) Idaho Power to use the Shared Facilities and TPIF as necessary for it to be able to operate its Project and to deliver to and receive energy from (x) the Black Mesa Project and (y) Idaho Power's transmission system; and NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows: AGREEMENT 1. TERM; EARLY TERMINATION 1.1. Term . The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, (b) as the result of a default by Idaho Power; or (c) concurrent with the expiration or termination of the Black Mesa GIA. 1.2. Conditions to Service . Black Mesa Interconnection shall be under no obligation to provide either Project with use of the Shared Facilities for purposes of transmitting power to the transmission grid unless and until the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("FERC") has accepted this Agreement for filing under Federal Power Action Section 205 without imposing any condition that Black Mesa Interconnection finds unacceptable, in its sole discretion. Black Mesa Interconnection shall be under no obligation to provide Idaho Power with use of the Shared Facilities for purposes of transmitting power to the transmission grid unless and until the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project is undergoing testing for energization. Idaho Power and Black Mesa shall each have access to the Shared Facilities for purposes of developing, constructing and operating their respective Project and taking station service for those reasons. In all cases throughout the term, subject to the terms and conditions of the PPA, Idaho Power's rights to utilize the Shared Facilities shall be subject to Black Mesa's priority rights to utilize the Shared Faculties for its purposes. 1.3. Right of First Offer . Upon early termination as the result of a default by Black Mesa Interconnection, each of Black Mesa and Idaho Power shall have the right of first offer to purchase, or otherwise obtain for use, a co-tenancy interest in the Shared Facilities sufficient to transmit energy from their respective Project to the transmission grid and take station service, and in the case of the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project, transmit charging energy from the grid to the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project, subject to negotiating a purchase and co-tenancy agreement with Black Mesa Interconnection, Black Mesa or any successor and obtaining the approval, if needed, from the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. 2. GRANT OF INTERCONNECTION AND SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS 2.1. Grant . Subject to Section 1.2 above, Black Mesa Interconnection grants to (a) Idaho Power, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, a non-exclusive, royalty-free, irrevocable (except as otherwise set forth in this Agreement) right and license to access and use the Shared Facilities as is necessary and convenient under the Black Mesa GIA to interconnect the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project to the Transmission System as part of the Large Generating Facility defined in the Black Mesa GIA, including for purposes of injecting electric energy from the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project or the Black Mesa Project into the Transmission System and the withdrawal of energy, if any, by the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project from the Transmission System or charging from the Black Mesa Project and otherwise utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with the Interconnection Service (as defined in the Black Mesa GIA) and ownership, operation and maintenance of the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project and (b) Black Mesa, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, a non-exclusive, royalty-free, irrevocable (except as otherwise set forth in this Agreement) right and license to access and use the Shared Facilities as is necessary and convenient to (i) connect its Project to the Shared Facilities, (ii) interconnect its Project to the Transmission System, use the Interconnection Service and inject electricity from its Project to the Transmission System, (iii) receive station service for its Project, and (iv) own, operate, maintain, repair, and use its Project. The grant of rights under this Agreement by Black Mesa Interconnection to Idaho Power and Black Mesa is made only to the extent that such rights do not limit in any material respect the ability of (i) Black Mesa Interconnection, as the Interconnection Customer under the Black Mesa GIA, to comply with, and take all steps necessary to remain in compliance with, the terms and conditions of the Black Mesa GIA or (ii) Black Mesa to perform its obligations under the PPA or any offtake agreement. All rights not expressly granted to Idaho Power or Black Mesa are reserved for Black Mesa Interconnection as owner of the Shared Facilities. 2.2. Essential Nature /Priority. Each Party hereby acknowledges that each of (i) the right of Idaho Power to access and utilize Black Mesa Interconnection's rights under the Black Mesa GIA and the Shared Facilities are essential to the injection of electric energy from the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project to the Transmission System and withdrawal of energy, if any, by the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project from the Transmission System, including for purposes of injecting electric energy from the Idaho Power Storage Project into the Transmission System and the withdrawal of energy, if any, by the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project from the Transmission System or charging from the PV Project and (ii) the right of Black Mesa to access and utilize Black Mesa's Interconnection's rights under the Black Mesa GIA and the Shared Facilities are essential to the injection of electric energy from the Black Mesa Project into the Transmission System and withdrawal of energy by Black Mesa for station service. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary herein, except as may be provided under the PPA, as between Black Mesa and Idaho Power, Black Mesa has priority to the transmission capacity in, and use of, the Shared Facilities. 2.3. Vesting . The right to access and utilize Black Mesa Interconnection's rights under the Black Mesa GIA and the Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Black Mesa Interconnection to Idaho Power and Black Mesa shall vest in each of Idaho Power and Black Mesa as contracting parties hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold or other interest or rights in the Shared Facilities. 3. NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS 3.1. Nature of Services . The Parties acknowledge that the grant of rights under this Agreement by Black Mesa Interconnection to Idaho Power and Black Mesa is required by the Black Mesa GIA and is made for the purpose of enabling the energy from each Project to reach the Transmission System, and enabling the energy from the Transmission System to reach each Project. The same is also necessary to facilitate the delivery of energy from the Black Mesa Project to the Idaho Power Energy Storage Facility. Subject to Section 2.1 herein, the grant of rights under this Agreement by Black Mesa Interconnection to Idaho Power and Black Mesa is not intended, for the avoidance of doubt, (i) to adversely affect the operations of the Black Mesa Project in any respect, or (ii) to limit the ability of any Party to perform its obligations under any agreement, as the same may hereafter be modified or amended, that such Party has entered into or enters into after the date hereof. 3.2. Obligations of Black Mesa Interconnection. Black Mesa Interconnection shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner consistent with its obligations under the Black Mesa GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Black Mesa Interconnection agrees to serve as the Shared Facilities Manager to: (i) perform its obligations under this Agreement and its obligations as the Interconnection Customer under the Black Mesa GIA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the Black Mesa GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the Black Mesa GIA; (ii) comply with all provisions of the Black Mesa GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, payments due, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof); (iii) serve as a single point of contact for Idaho Power and Black Mesa under the Black Mesa GIA, and to promptly provide to Idaho Power and Black Mesa any material notices it receives under the Black Mesa GIA; (iv) perform necessary maintenance on the Shared Facilities; and (v) construct the Shared Facilities to facilitate the delivery and/or receipt of energy to the Idaho Power Transmission System on or before June 1, 2023, independent of whether the Black Mesa Project is constructed or operational by that same date. 3.3. Obligations of Idaho Power and Black Mesa. Each of Black Mesa and Idaho Power shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates Black Mesa Interconnection's performance under, and compliance with, the Black Mesa GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, each of Black Mesa and Idaho Power agrees to: (i) operate its Project and perform its obligations under this Agreement in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the Black Mesa GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the Black Mesa GIA; (ii) facilitate Black Mesa Interconnection's compliance with all provisions of the Black Mesa GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as related to its Project; (iii) not take any action (or refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the Black Mesa GIA by Black Mesa Interconnection; (iv) use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of its Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default by Black Mesa Interconnection under the Black Mesa GIA, and if such default occurs or is determined by Black Mesa Interconnection in good faith to be reasonably likely to result in such default, promptly assist Black Mesa Interconnection in curing such default in accordance with the terms of the Black Mesa GIA; (v) comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by Black Mesa Interconnection, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the Black Mesa GIA; (vi) provide Black Mesa Interconnection with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of its Project required for Black Mesa Interconnection to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the Black Mesa GIA; and (vii) promptly provide to Black Mesa Interconnection copies of all notices and instructions received by it that affect Black Mesa Interconnection's performance under the Black Mesa GIA. 3.4. Curtailment . Neither Black Mesa nor Idaho Power shall operate its respective Project in such a manner as to interfere with the other Party's operation and ability to deliver or receive energy by use of the Shared Facilities, except, to the extent a PPA is in effect, as expressly provided with respect to Non-Compensable and Compensable Curtailment as those terms are defined and addressed in the PPA. For other such disruptions, disconnections, outages, or curtailments due to the actions or inactions of a Party that is not excused by an event of force majeure and, to the extent a PPA is in effect, is not Non-Compensable or Compensable Curtailment as defined in the PPA, the offending Party shall be responsible for (a) the other Party's lost revenues, including all revenues that such Party would have earned for energy, green attributes, capacity, tax incentives or credits on a grossed-up basis, or other products it would have sold under the applicable agreements to which it is a party, (b) availability incentive or bonus payments lost, or (c) other liabilities, damages, penalties, costs or charges incurred by such Party as a direct result of any disruptions, disconnections, outages, interruptions or curtailments of output. In each case payment shall be provided within ten (10) business days following receipt of demand therefor, and in each case, such payments made or to be made shall be reduced by any insurance proceeds actually received in connection with the events described in subclauses (a), (b), or (c) of this Section 3.4. Except as may be dictated by the PPA, (x) to the extent that any curtailment or other reduction of capacity on the transmission system impacts the Projects and is not the result of the actions or omissions of a Party, such curtailment shall be allocated first to Idaho Power and then to Black Mesa, and (y) to the extent any curtailment is specific to a Project or Projects or is the result of the actions or omissions of a Party, the curtailment shall be allocated first to such Project. 3.5. No Joint and Several Liability between Black Mesa Interconnection, Black Mesa and Idaho Power . The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject any Party to joint and several liability for any actions taken by any other Party. 3.6. Assignment or Transfer of Rights . Except as set forth in this Agreement, Black Mesa Interconnection shall not grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right to any third party with regard to the Shared Facilities, and no Party shall assign or transfer any rights granted to it hereunder with regard to the Shared Facilities, without the prior written consent of the other Parties, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed. 3.7. Interference . Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities if the exercise of such rights would materially interfere with or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party. 3.8. Prior Written Consent . Except as set forth in this Agreement or as may be required of Black Mesa or Black Mesa Interconnection by a lender or investor in its exercise of remedies, without the prior written consent of each other Party, no Party shall take any action that results in (i) the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights of the other Parties or (ii) increases the obligations or responsibilities of the other Parties, in each case, with respect to such Party's access to, utilization of or reliance upon the Shared Facilities. 4. MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES; SUCCESSOR AGREEMENT; METERING 4.1. Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses . (i) Black Mesa Interconnection shall be solely responsible for the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities, including (a) the costs and expenses of the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities and of insuring the Shared Facilities, and (b) the costs that Black Mesa Interconnection is responsible for under the Black Mesa GIA, including potential costs under Section 10.5 for operations and maintenance expenses. (ii) Black Mesa and Idaho Power shall each be liable to pay for the station power service of their respective Projects. 4.2. Successor Agreement . In the event that the Shared Facilities are no longer operated and maintained only by Black Mesa Interconnection for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities provided that such agreement remains generally consistent with the principles granting each Party access to the transmission system and delivery of energy. 4.3. Further Assurances . Each Party hereto covenants and agrees to promptly work in good faith to do and perform such other and further acts and things as any other Party hereto may reasonably request or as may be otherwise be necessary or proper to resolve the appropriate allocation of the following items among the Projects: (A) the energy output and usage of the applicable Projects, (B) associated losses, and (C) payments associated with the Projects' energy output, usage, and losses. 4.4. Management Fee . Within thirty (30) days after the Commercial Operation Date (as defined in the Black Mesa GIA), and recurring on the anniversary of the Commercial Operation Date thereafter, Idaho Power shall pay Black Mesa Interconnection an annual management fee of twenty thousand dollars ($20,000), increasing by 2.0% per year. 5. CHANGE IN LAW 5.1. Change in Law . In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Shared Facilities, any of the Projects, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. 6. CERTAIN COVENANTS 6.1. Authority and Operational Abilities . Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. 6.2. Agreement to Cooperate . Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Parties so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each such Project. 6.3. Adverse Events . (i) If an operational issue arises at the Black Mesa Project or Idaho Power Energy Storage Project that is reasonably expected to result in a material breach by Black Mesa Interconnection of the Black Mesa GIA or this Agreement or if required to comply with any applicable Tariff requirements of Idaho Power (as defined in the Black Mesa GIA) (an "Adverse Event"), Black Mesa Interconnection shall first curtail the Project that is causing the Adverse Event and then the other Project as necessary. In the event of such curtailment, energy deliveries to or withdrawals from the Point of Interconnection from the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall be limited as necessary until the Adverse Event has been resolved in the reasonable judgment of Black Mesa Interconnection. (ii) If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event caused by a Project, Black Mesa or Idaho Power, as applicable, incurs costs, expenses, damages, losses, liabilities or penalties of any kind ("AE Costs"), the Party owning the Project that caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for such AE Costs. In the event that both Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that Black Mesa Interconnection, in its sole and absolute discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, such AE Costs shall be allocated accordingly. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Black Mesa Interconnection, as determined in its sole and absolute discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, Black Mesa shall be liable for 50% of such AE Costs and Idaho Power shall be liable for 50% of such AE Costs. 6.4. Withdrawal. In the event that either Idaho Power or Black Mesa determines that it will cease operation of or otherwise abandon its Project, such Party shall have the right to withdraw from this Agreement without affecting the other Party's right to use the Shared Facilities, subject to payment of any amount due and owing and satisfaction of all other obligations and liabilities through the effective date of its withdrawal. 6.5. Financing Cooperation. Each Party agrees that it shall cooperate with the reasonable requests of each other Party in connection with the financing or refinancing, including tax equity financing, of its respective Project and the Shared Facilities, including the execution of customary estoppels, consents for the benefit of the financing parties, and other similar agreements as may be reasonably requested by a Party, and making such amendments to this Agreement as reasonably requested by a financing party. 6.6. Access Rights. (i) Black Mesa and Idaho Power each represents that it holds or will hold sufficient real property rights (by fee, lease, easement, rights of way, or otherwise) to its respective project site for its respective Project (each such project site, a "Project Site"). (ii) Black Mesa will grant a license or sublease to Black Mesa Interconnection for the construction, installation, ownership, operation, maintenance and repair of the Shared Facilities on its Project Site. (iii) Black Mesa will consent to and reasonably cooperate, at Idaho Power's cost and expense, with the fee owner of its Project Site and Idaho Power to grant to Idaho Power the right to cross over, under and onto the Black Mesa's Project Site for the purpose of connecting the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project to the Shared Facilities. (iv) Each Party hereby grants to the other Parties, the right of ingress and egress to and from its Project Site (to the extent such rights are held by the granting Party), solely to the extent required to exercise such Party's rights and perform its obligations with respect to the Shared Facilities and subject to the requirement that each Party (i) will provide reasonable advance notice to the other Parties, (ii) will not unreasonably interfere with the business operations of the other Parties, and (iii) will adhere to the other Party's safety and conduct rules and procedures. 7. MATERIAL BREACH; LIMITATIONS 7.1. Material Breach by any Party . In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party fails to promptly cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from a non-defaulting Party describing such breach, each non-defaulting Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the defaulting Party, (ii) if Black Mesa Interconnection is a non-breaching Party, suspend the defaulting Party's access to all or any portion of the Shared Facilities for so long as such default shall be continuing and remain uncured and disconnect the defaulting Party's Project from the Shared Facilities, or (iii) revoke the defaulting Party's license hereunder. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in the event that a breach of this Agreement could give rise to a breach by Black Mesa Interconnection pursuant to the terms of the Black Mesa GIA, no non-defaulting Party shall be required to provide the defaulting Party with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedies specified in clause (i) or (ii) above; provided, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender or investor of such Party. Each Party expressly acknowledges and agrees that a lender or investor, upon notice to all Parties, may cure a breach of any defaulting Party. If a Party (or any lender or investor thereof) chooses to cure a Party's default, the defaulting Party shall reimburse each non-defaulting Party (or such Party's lender or investor) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by such non-defaulting Party (or such Party's lender or investor) in curing such default. 7.2. Except for indemnification obligations related to third-party claims as provided for in Section 9.6 or as otherwise expressly provided for in this Agreement, including Section 3.4 and Section 6.3(ii), in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages including, but not limited to, loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability. 8. FORCE MAJEURE 8.1. Force Majeure . Upon any occurrence beyond a Party's reasonable control that prevents such Party from fulfilling an obligation under this Agreement and that would constitute an event of Force Majeure (as defined in the Black Mesa GIA), such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement to the extent caused directly or indirectly thereby. The Party affected shall promptly give notice and the full particulars of such Force Majeure (as defined in the Black Mesa GIA) to the other Parties in writing or by telephone as soon as reasonably possible after the occurrence of the cause relied upon. Telephone notices given pursuant to this article shall be confirmed in writing as soon as reasonably possible and shall specifically state full particulars of such Force Majeure, the time and date when such Force Majeure occurred and when such Force Majeure is reasonably expected to cease. The Party affected shall exercise due diligence to remove such disability with reasonable dispatch, but shall not be required to accede or agree to any provision not satisfactory to it in order to settle and terminate a strike or other labor disturbance. 9. MISCELLANEOUS 9.1. Authorization . Except as provided in Section 7.1, nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party. 9.2. Modification and Amendment . The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all Parties. 9.3. Waiver . The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party's right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. 9.4. Enforceability . Any provision of this Agreement, which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof. 9.5. Assignment . No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of the other Party, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld, conditioned, or delayed, provided, however, that any Party may, without the consent of each other Party, collaterally assign this Agreement to any investor or lender in connection with a financing or refinancing of, or investment in, the Projects. 9.6. Indemnification . Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party's willful misconduct, intentional wrongdoing, fraud, or grossly negligent performance or non-performance of its obligations under this Agreement,, except to the extent of fraud, gross negligence, willful misconduct or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified Party. 9.7. Choice of Law, Jurisdiction and Waiver of Jury Trial . (i) This Agreement and the rights and obligations of the Parties hereunder will be governed pursuant to, and enforced, construed and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the State of Idaho without regard to principles of conflicts of laws. Venue for resolution of any disputes under this Agreement shall be Ada County, Idaho. (ii) Each of the Parties irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York for the purposes of any suit, action or other proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement, the transactions contemplated hereby, any provision hereof or the breach, performance, enforcement or validity or invalidity of this Agreement or any provision hereof (and agrees not to commence any suit, action or proceeding relating thereto except in such courts). (iii) THE PARTIES HERETO EACH HEREBY KNOWINGLY, VOLUNTARILY AND INTENTIONALLY WAIVE THE RIGHT EACH MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY WITH RESPECT TO ANY PROCEEDINGS BASED HEREON, OR ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT, OR ANY COURSE OF CONDUCT, COURSE OF DEALING, STATEMENTS (WHETHER ORAL OR WRITTEN) OR ACTIONS OF EITHER PARTY TO THIS AGREEMENT. THIS PROVISION IS A MATERIAL INDUCEMENT FOR THE PARTIES TO ENTER INTO THIS AGREEMENT. 9.8. Inspection of Records . Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice, at reasonable times, and respecting the potential confidentiality and any requisite confidentiality agreements and/or procedures necessary safeguard the same. 9.9. Entire Agreement . This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. 9.10. Section Headings . The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. 9.11. Counterparts . This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. 9.12. Specific Performance . The Parties hereto may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance. A facsimile or Portable Document Format (".pdf") signature page shall constitute an original for purposes hereof. 9.13. Obligation to Notify in Case of Termination . The Parties shall notify Idaho Power Transmission Provider within 10 business days if the Agreement is terminated. 9.14. Insurance . At all times during the term of this Agreement, each of Idaho Power and Black Mesa shall maintain insurance as then required under the Black Mesa GIA. 9.15. Memorandum. Upon the request of any Party from time to time, the Parties shall execute and deliver one or more memorandums of this Agreement sufficient to set forth this Agreement as a matter of record. Any Party may, at it sole cost and expense, record any such memorandum in Elmore County, Idaho. If any memorandum of this Agreement has been recorded, then at such time as this Agreement has been terminated, the Parties agree to execute and record in the official real estate records of the county referred to above, a termination of all memorandums of this Agreement, which termination will specifically refer to the memorandum(s) of this Agreement and will recite that this Agreement has terminated in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement.

The "Shared Facilities" shall consist of * Rights to access the Transmission System pursuant to the Black Mesa GIA, including the Interconnection Customer's Interconnection Facilities and Transmission Provider's Interconnection Facilities. * Collector substation o Main Power Transformer, 34.5kV circuit breakers, 138kV circuit breakers, control building, CT's and PT's, metering, relays, switches, steel structures, bus work, and other components and equipment associated with the electrical connection, protection and control, and transmission of power through the collector substation including the same for connection of the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project. * Gen-tie line connecting the collector substation to the Interconnection Customer's Interconnection Facilities and Transmission Provider Interconnection Facilities. * SCADA o Switches, power plant controller, UPS, firewall, and all other equipment, components, and software necessary to control, dispatch, communicate, and report to and from the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project for the mutually agreed operations of the Black Mesa Project and the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project. For the avoidance of doubt, Idaho Power will have sole control and dispatch of the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project in accordance with this Agreement. Nothing in this Agreement will provide Black Mesa with direct access to or control of the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project. * Weather stations * Telecom access * Access road * Fencing * Water facilities * The Shared Facilities will be constructed, owned, and operated with sufficient capacity to ensure the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project can deliver 40MWac to the Transmission Provider Interconnection Facilities. * Idaho Power is responsible to construct facilities between the Idaho Power Energy Storage Project and the Shared Facilities generally defined as a 34.5kV bus connection or switch.
